                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d813">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.18/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-23T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your 61 October 18, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>If there is any doubt under Costa Rican law or regulations as to validity
                    resubmission extradition convention it would be preferable to sign new
                    convention. Full power being sent you.<note n="14" xml:id="d813fn14">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1108" n="988" xml:id="pg_988"/>
                <p>In connection with ratification Foreign Office should apparently address note to
                    you in terms similar to those employed in Portuguese note page 1475 Malloy’s
                    Treaty Compilation, your reply to which would follow lines of Department’s
                    answer to Portuguese note set out page 1476.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
